 {"id":"bd-1qfv","title":"Saga executor: compensating transactions for multi-step operations","description":"# Saga Executor Implementation

## Goal

Implement the saga pattern for multi-step distributed operations with compensating transactions, providing transactional guarantees without distributed locking.

## Background

Traditional distributed transactions (2PC) have problems:
- Blocking: participants hold locks until coordinator decides
- Single point of failure: coordinator crash blocks all
- Not partition tolerant: network split causes indefinite blocking

Sagas solve this with compensation:
- Each step has a forward action and a compensating action
- If step N fails, run compensations for steps 1..N-1
- Eventually consistent, not immediately consistent

## Core Types

### Saga
```rust
pub struct Saga<Ctx> {
    /// Unique saga identifier
    id: SagaId,

    /// Steps to execute in order
    steps: Vec<SagaStep<Ctx>>,

    /// Current execution state
    state: SagaState,

    /// Context passed through steps
    context: Ctx,

    /// Idempotency token for the saga
    token: IdempotencyToken,
}

pub struct SagaStep<Ctx> {
    /// Step name (for logging/debugging)
    name: &'static str,

    /// Forward action
    action: Box<dyn SagaAction<Ctx>>,

    /// Compensating action (undo)
    compensation: Box<dyn SagaCompensation<Ctx>>,

    /// Step state
    state: StepState,

    /// Result of action (if completed)
    result: Option<StepResult>,
}
```

### SagaState
```rust
pub enum SagaState {
    /// Not started yet
    Pending,

    /// Executing forward actions
    Executing { current_step: usize },

    /// All steps completed successfully
    Completed,

    /// A step failed, running compensations
    Compensating { failed_at: usize, compensating: usize },

    /// All compensations complete
    Aborted { reason: Error },

    /// Compensation also failed (manual intervention needed)
    CompensationFailed { step: usize, error: Error },
}

pub enum StepState {
    Pending,
    Running,
    Completed,
    Failed(Error),
    Compensating,
    Compensated,
    CompensationFailed(Error),
}
```

### SagaAction / SagaCompensation
```rust
#[async_trait]
pub trait SagaAction<Ctx>: Send + Sync {
    type Output: Serialize + DeserializeOwned;

    async fn execute(&self, ctx: &mut Ctx, cx: &mut Cx) -> Outcome<Self::Output, Error>;
}

#[async_trait]
pub trait SagaCompensation<Ctx>: Send + Sync {
    type Input;  // Output of the action being compensated

    async fn compensate(&self, input: &Self::Input, ctx: &mut Ctx, cx: &mut Cx) -> Result<(), Error>;
}
```

## SagaExecutor

```rust
pub struct SagaExecutor {
    /// Saga persistence (for crash recovery)
    store: Box<dyn SagaStore>,

    /// Idempotency registry
    idempotency: Arc<IdempotencyRegistry>,

    /// Configuration
    config: SagaConfig,
}

impl SagaExecutor {
    /// Execute a saga to completion
    pub async fn execute<Ctx>(&self, saga: Saga<Ctx>, cx: &mut Cx) -> SagaResult<Ctx>;

    /// Resume a saga after crash
    pub async fn resume(&self, saga_id: SagaId, cx: &mut Cx) -> SagaResult<()>;

    /// Get saga status
    pub fn status(&self, saga_id: SagaId) -> Option<SagaState>;

    /// Force compensation (manual abort)
    pub async fn abort(&self, saga_id: SagaId, cx: &mut Cx) -> Result<(), Error>;
}
```

## Persistence

Saga state must be persisted for crash recovery:
```rust
#[async_trait]
pub trait SagaStore: Send + Sync {
    async fn save(&self, saga: &SagaRecord) -> Result<(), Error>;
    async fn load(&self, id: SagaId) -> Result<Option<SagaRecord>, Error>;
    async fn list_incomplete(&self) -> Result<Vec<SagaId>, Error>;
}

pub struct SagaRecord {
    id: SagaId,
    state: SagaState,
    steps: Vec<StepRecord>,
    context_bytes: Vec<u8>,
    created_at: Time,
    updated_at: Time,
}
```

## Example: Money Transfer Saga

```rust
let saga = Saga::new()
    .step(
        'debit_source',
        DebitAction { account: source, amount },
        CreditAction { account: source, amount },  // Compensation
    )
    .step(
        'credit_destination',
        CreditAction { account: dest, amount },
        DebitAction { account: dest, amount },  // Compensation
    )
    .step(
        'record_transfer',
        RecordAction { from: source, to: dest, amount },
        DeleteRecordAction { ... },  // Compensation
    );

let result = executor.execute(saga, cx).await;
```

## Compensation Strategies

### Forward Recovery
Try to complete failed step (retry with backoff):
```rust
pub struct RetryConfig {
    max_attempts: u32,
    backoff: BackoffStrategy,
}
```

### Backward Recovery
Run compensations for completed steps.

### Hybrid
Retry N times, then compensate.

## Integration with Asupersync

- SagaExecutor runs in a region
- Each step runs as a separate task with its own budget
- Cancellation triggers compensation
- Steps use idempotency tokens for safe retry
- Leases held during saga execution

## Testing

- Happy path: all steps complete
- Failure: step N fails, compensate 1..N-1
- Crash recovery: resume incomplete saga
- Compensation failure: mark for manual intervention
- Cancellation: treat as failure, compensate

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Saga and SagaStep types
- [ ] SagaState with all transitions
- [ ] SagaAction and SagaCompensation traits
- [ ] SagaExecutor with execute/resume/abort
- [ ] SagaStore trait for persistence
- [ ] Retry strategy for forward recovery
- [ ] Compensation execution logic
