Current state: Asupersync uses std::fs with blocking pool wrappers. This works
but adds overhead and latency. Tokio users will say 'tokio::fs provides async
file operations' - we should have better.

## Current State
- io_uring exists as optional feature
- File operations wrapped in blocking pool
- No true async file I/O

## Target Architecture
```rust
/// Async file with io_uring backend.
