 {"id":"bd-1r6o","title":"Obligation leak detection: runtime enforcement and diagnostics","description":"# Obligation Leak Detection

## Goal

Implement comprehensive runtime detection and diagnostics for obligation leaks, ensuring the 'no obligation leaks' invariant is enforceable.

## Background

Asupersync's obligation system tracks linear resources:
- SendPermit: Reserved channel slot
- Ack: Message acknowledgement
- Lease: Remote resource claim
- IoOp: Pending I/O operation

Obligations MUST be resolved (committed or aborted) before the holder completes. A 'leak' is when a task completes while still holding an obligation.

## Current State

The codebase has:
- ObligationRecord in src/record/obligation.rs
- Various dialect implementations (dialectica, graded, guarded, etc.)
- Placeholder leak detection

Missing:
- Runtime enforcement on task completion
- Diagnostic messages with source locations
- Integration with all obligation types
- Lab oracle for testing

## Detection Points

### 1. Task Completion
When a task reaches terminal state, check for held obligations.

### 2. Region Close
When a region closes, all tasks must have resolved obligations.

### 3. Cancellation Drain
During cancellation, obligations must be resolved in drain phase.

## Diagnostic Information

ObligationLeakError includes:
- task: TaskId that leaked
- obligations: Vec<LeakedObligation>
- completion: CompletionReason

LeakedObligation includes:
- id: ObligationId
- kind: ObligationKind
- acquired_at: SourceLocation (file, line, column)
- acquire_trace: Option<Backtrace> (debug mode)
- held_duration: Duration

## Acquisition Tracking

Use #[track_caller] to capture source locations:
```rust
impl ObligationRegistry {
    #[track_caller]
    pub fn reserve(&mut self, kind: ObligationKind, holder: TaskId) -> ObligationId {
        let location = std::panic::Location::caller();
        // ... create record with location
    }
}
```

## Leak Responses

- Debug Mode: Panic with full diagnostic
- Release Mode: Convert to Outcome::Panicked, log warning
- Lab Mode: Record in trace, available via oracle

## ObligationLeakOracle

```rust
pub struct ObligationLeakOracle {
    leaks: Vec<ObligationLeakError>,
}

impl Oracle for ObligationLeakOracle {
    fn check(&self, runtime: &RuntimeState) -> OracleResult {
        if self.leaks.is_empty() {
            OracleResult::Pass
        } else {
            OracleResult::Fail(format\!(...))
        }
    }
}
```

