```
tests/
├── obligation/
│   ├── mod.rs
│   ├── unit/
│   │   ├── registry.rs           # Reserve/commit/abort
│   │   ├── source_location.rs    # #[track_caller] works
│   │   └── leak_detection.rs     # Detection logic
│   ├── integration/
│   │   ├── task_completion.rs    # Leak on task complete
│   │   ├── region_close.rs       # Leak blocks region close
│   │   ├── cancellation.rs       # Drain resolves obligations
│   │   └── oracle.rs             # Oracle integration
│   └── e2e/
│       ├── channel_permit.rs     # SendPermit scenarios
│       ├── multi_obligation.rs   # Multiple obligations
│       └── nested_regions.rs     # Obligations in nested regions
```

## Logging Requirements

```rust
error\!(
    event = 'obligation_leak',
    task_id = %task_id,
    obligation_id = %ob.id,
    kind = ?ob.kind,
    acquired_at = %ob.acquired_at,
    held_duration_ms = ob.held_duration.as_millis(),
    'Obligation leaked on task completion'
);
```

## Test Cases

### Unit Tests
- reserve() returns ObligationId
- commit() resolves obligation
- abort() resolves obligation
- #[track_caller] captures correct location

### Integration Tests
- Task completes with obligation -> leak detected
- Task aborts obligation correctly -> no leak
- Region close with leaked obligation -> blocked
- Cancellation with obligation -> drain must resolve

### E2E Tests
